Beau Vallon of Mauritius Buys Rival Union Sugar Estates, L’Express Reports

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-05-03T06:48:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/beau-vallon-of-mauritius-buys-rival-union-sugar-estates-l-express-reports.html
Compagnie de Beau Vallon Ltd., a
sugar-cane producer in Mauritius, has bought rival Union Sugar
Estates Co., l’Express reported, citing an unidentified person
involved in the transaction.  Union, which has interests from sugar plantations to
property and tourism, has a value of about 840 million rupees
($30.7 million) based on its net asset value per share,
according to the  Port Louis-based newspaper .  Thierry Merven, a manager for Compagnie de Beau Vallon,
wasn’t available to comment when Bloomberg News called his
office in Saint Hubert, in the southern part of Mauritius. Union
Sugar manager Denis Lavoipierre didn’t return calls to his
office in Riviere des Anguilles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
